<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8221739>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Afrithelphusa afzelii (Colosi 1924), adult ♂ CW 25.0 mm, ZMB Crust. 34,607, from Moyamba District, Sierra Leone: a, carapace, frontal view; d, thoracic sternum, h, mandible frontal view. Afrithelphusa gerhildae Bott, 1969, adult ♂ CW 22.5 mm, SMF 2619a, Le Voile de la Mariée, Kindia, Guinea: e, thoracic sternum, i, mandible frontal view (Cumberlidge 1999, fig. 48A). Afrithelphusa leonensis (Cumberlidge, 1987), adult ♂, CW 26.4 mm, ZMB Crust. 34,606, from Guma Lake, Sugar Loaf Mountain, Sierra Leone: b, carapace, frontal view; f, thoracic sternum, j, mandible frontal view. Afrithelphusa monodosa (Bott, 1969), adult ♂, CW 24.3 mm, NMU 24.IV.2005, Sarabaya, Guinea: c, carapace,frontal view; g, thoracic sternum, k, mandible, frontal view. Photographs a, c by P. A. Mvogo Ndongo; d by Neil Cumberlidge and Margaret Lorenz; e by Michael Türkay. Scale bar: a = 8.9 mm; b = 9.6 mm; c = 11.6 mm; d–g = 8.0 mm; h–k = 3.1 mm. CW = carapace width, ZMB = Museum für Naturkunde, Berlin, Germany, NMU = Northern Michigan University, USA." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8221739/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8221741>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Afrithelphusa afzelii (Colosi 1924), adult ♂ CW 25.0 mm, ZMB 34607, from Moyamba District, Sierra Leone: a, right cheliped, frontal view;b, left cheliped, frontal view;i, right cheliped carpus superior view; m, right cheliped merus superior view. Afrithelphusa gerhildae Bott, 1969, adult ♂ CW 22.5 mm, SMF 2619a, Le Voile de la Mariée, Kindia, Guinea: c, right cheliped, frontal view (Cumberlidge 1999, fig. 50A); d, left cheliped, frontal view (Cumberlidge 1999, fig. 50A); j, right cheliped carpus superior view; n, right cheliped merus superior view. Afrithelphusa leonensis (Cumberlidge, 1987), adult ♂, CW 26.4 mm, ZMB Crust. 34,606, from Guma Lake, Sugar Loaf Mountain, Sierra Leone: e, right cheliped, frontal view; f, left cheliped, frontal view; k, right cheliped carpus superior view; o, right cheliped merus superior view. Afrithelphusa monodosa (Bott, 1969), adult ♂, CW 24.3 mm, NMU 24.IV.2005, Sarabaya, Guinea: g, right cheliped, frontal view; h, left cheliped, frontal view; l, right cheliped carpus superior view; p, right cheliped merus superior view. Photographs a, b, e, f, i, k, m, o by P. A. Mvogo Ndongo; g, h, l, p by Neil Cumberlidge and Margaret Lorenz; j, n by Michael Türkay. Scale bar: a–h = 11.2 mm; i–p = 5.6 mm. CW = carapace width, ZMB = Museum für Naturkunde, Berlin, Germany, SMF = Senckenberg Museum, Frankfurt, Germany, NMU = Northern Michigan University, USA." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8221741/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8221745>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Afrithelphusa afzelii (Colosi 1924), adult ♂ CW 29.5 mm, SMNH 168, Sierra Leone: a, G1 ventral view; b, G2 ventral view; c, G1 dorsal view; m, third maxilliped, frontal view. Afrithelphusa gerhildae Bott, 1969, adult ♂ CW 22.5 mm, SMF 2619a, Le Voile de la Mariée, Kindia, Guinea: d, G1 ventral view; e, G2 ventral view (Cumberlidge 1999, fig. 53AA); f, G1 dorsal view (Cumberlidge 1999, fig. 52B); n, third maxilliped, frontal view (Cumberlidge 1999, fig. 49A). Afrithelphusa leonensis (Cumberlidge, 1987), adult ♂, CW 26.4 mm, ZMB Crust. 34,606, from Guma Lake, Sugar Loaf Mountain, Sierra Leone: g, G1 ventral view; h, G2 ventral view; i, G1 dorsal view; o, third maxilliped, frontal view.Afrithelphusa monodosa (Bott, 1969), adult ♂, CW 24.3 mm, NMU 24.IV.2005, Sarabaya, Guinea: j, G1 ventral view; k, G2 ventral view; l, G1 dorsal view; p, third maxilliped,frontal view. Photographs a–c, g–i, m, o by P. A. Mvogo Ndongo; j–l, p by Neil Cumberlidge and Margaret Lorenz;d by Michael Türkay.Scale bar:a, c, d, f, g, i, j, l = 10.0 mm; b, e, h, k = 5.8 mm; m–p = 2.4 mm. CW = carapace width, SMNH = Swedish Museum of Natural History, Stockholm,Sweden,G1 = gonopod 1, G2 = gonopod 2, ZMB = Museum für Naturkunde,Berlin,Germany, SMF = Senckenberg Museum, Frankfurt, Germany, NMU = Northern Michigan University, USA." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8221745/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

